<section class="hero">
<div class="container">
	<div class="hero-eyebrow">
		<span class="eyebrow-pill">v0.1.0</span>
		<span class="eyebrow-text">// agentskills.io open standard</span>
	</div>
	<h1>
		The developer toolkit<br />for <span class="accent">agent skills</span>.
		<span class="line2">Build, validate, route, and generate SKILL.md files — the portable format for AI agent capabilities.</span>
	</h1>
	<p class="hero-sub">
		<code>SKILL.md</code> is a <strong>markdown file</strong> that teaches an AI agent one capability.
		This toolkit lets you parse, validate, lint, score, route, and generate them — <strong>no LLM required</strong>.
	</p>
	<div class="hero-actions">
		<a href="https://github.com/skill-tools/skill-tools" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-fill">npm install skill-tools <span class="btn-arrow">&darr;</span></a>
		<a href="/docs/core" class="btn btn-outline">Read the Docs <span class="btn-arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
	</div>

	<div class="what-grid">
		<div class="what-item">
			<div class="what-num">WHAT</div>
			<h3>SKILL.md</h3>
			<p>A markdown file with YAML frontmatter that describes one capability an agent can perform.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="what-item">
			<div class="what-num">WHY</div>
			<h3>Portable skills</h3>
			<p>One format, any agent. Share skills across teams, vendors, and frameworks.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="what-item">
			<div class="what-num">HOW</div>
			<h3>This toolkit</h3>
			<p>Parse, validate, lint, score, route by intent, and auto-generate from OpenAPI specs.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
</section>

<style>
	.hero {
		position: relative;
		z-index: 10;
		padding: 10rem 0 5rem;
		min-height: 100vh;
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
	}

	.hero .container { width: 100%; }

	.hero-eyebrow {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.75rem;
		margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
	}

	.eyebrow-pill {
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		font-size: 0.72rem;
		color: var(--green);
		border: 1px solid rgba(62, 207, 142, 0.25);
		padding: 0.35em 0.85em;
		border-radius: 50px;
		background: rgba(62, 207, 142, 0.06);
		letter-spacing: 0.02em;
	}

	.eyebrow-text {
		font-size: 0.82rem;
		color: var(--dim);
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 6rem);
		letter-spacing: -0.05em;
		line-height: 1;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	h1 .accent { color: var(--green); }

	h1 .line2 {
		display: block;
		color: var(--muted);
		font-size: 0.48em;
		font-weight: 500;
		letter-spacing: -0.01em;
		margin-top: 0.4em;
		line-height: 1.4;
		font-family: var(--font-body);
	}

	.hero-sub {
		color: var(--muted);
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		max-width: 540px;
		line-height: 1.8;
		margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
	}

	.hero-sub strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; }

	.hero-actions {
		display: flex;
		gap: 0.75rem;
		align-items: center;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		margin-bottom: 4rem;
	}

	.what-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 1px;
		background: var(--border);
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
		max-width: 760px;
	}

	.what-item { background: var(--bg); padding: 1.5rem 1.6rem; }

	.what-num {
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		font-size: 0.6rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.what-item:nth-child(1) .what-num { color: var(--green); }
	.what-item:nth-child(2) .what-num { color: var(--pink); }
	.what-item:nth-child(3) .what-num { color: var(--orange); }

	.what-item h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.3rem; }
	.what-item p { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.5; }

	@media (max-width: 900px) { .what-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.hero { padding: 7rem 0 4rem; min-height: auto; }
		h1 { font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 10vw, 4rem); }
		.hero-actions { width: 100%; }
		.hero-actions :global(.btn) { width: 100%; justify-content: center; }
	}
</style>
